text: Cecily Edith Mary Cousens (1918-2008) was a female diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== Cousens won a bronze medal in the 10 Metres Platform at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. ==References== Category:1918 births Category:2008 deaths Category:English female divers Category:Divers at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in diving Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:People from Swindon
